1
00:00:08,040 --> 00:00:10,880
EDMUND: If I have not returned
in an hour, you must fetch the police.

2
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,120
Edmund!

3
00:00:13,280 --> 00:00:16,000
Don't fret, Effie, my dear,
all will be well.

4
00:00:16,080 --> 00:00:18,400
But we must get to the bottom of
this dark and queer business,

5
00:00:18,480 --> 00:00:20,760
no matter what the cost.

6
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:30,480
(DOOR CLOSES)

7
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:35,440
Mrs Gillyflower.

8
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:38,200
We have come about
your husband, my dear.

9
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:39,680
A tragedy.

10
00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:40,840
My husband?

11
00:00:40,920 --> 00:00:43,160
Your late husband.

12
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,680
There must be some mistake,
my husband is quite well.

13
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:50,960
(EDMUND SCREAMING)

14
00:00:55,560 --> 00:00:57,920
We're so very sorry for your loss.

15
00:00:58,640 --> 00:01:00,160
(EFFIE SCREAMS)

16
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:05,480
Oh, hellfire, that's put me
right off me mash. (LAUGHS)

17
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:08,400
-Another one.
-Another?

18
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:11,240
He's not the first one
I've had in here looking like that.

19
00:01:11,320 --> 00:01:14,320
The Crimson Horror,
that's what they're calling it.

20
00:01:15,440 --> 00:01:18,560
I have no interest in the deplorable
excesses of the penny dreadfuls.

21
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:21,560
Hey, hey. Payment in advance, flower.

22
00:01:26,680 --> 00:01:28,760
Taking a big risk, you see, I am.

23
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:30,840
They'll have me vitals
for fiddle strings

24
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:35,240
if they knew I'd let you come to
look at one of their precious stiffs.

25
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:38,320
This stiff is my brother.

26
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:41,000
I've come up from London
to bring him home.

27
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:42,200
Oh, aye?

28
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,480
MR THURSDAY: Thank you
for agreeing to this meeting.

29
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:48,080
I'm told you're the investigator to see
if there are strange goings-on.

30
00:01:48,440 --> 00:01:50,000
I read of your brother's death.

31
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:52,640
Another victim of the Crimson Horror,
I believe?

32
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:55,600
So it is claimed.
He was a newspaper man.

33
00:01:56,240 --> 00:01:58,320
He and a young woman
were working undercover.

34
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:00,240
Tell me, Madame,

35
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:03,200
-do you know what an Octagram is?
-(VASTRA CHUCKLES)

36
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:05,320
VASTRA: It's a silly superstition, sir.

37
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:09,160
The belief that the eye can retain
an image of the last thing it sees.

38
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,440
-Good grief!
-MR THURSDAY: Oh, gosh!

39
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:31,480
(THUDDING)

40
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:37,000
Well, I'll be blowed.

41
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:41,400
I think, Madame, that we'd better
make plans to head north.

42
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,760
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

43
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:26,800
According to my research,
Sweetville's proprietor

44
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:29,680
holds recruitment try-outs
for her little community.

45
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:33,640
She is only interested in the fittest
and the most beautiful.

46
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:35,880
You may rely on me, ma'am.

47
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:40,360
I was, in fact, speaking to Jenny.

48
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:43,240
Jenny.

49
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:48,840
If this weak and fleshy boy
is to represent us...

50
00:03:48,920 --> 00:03:50,520
-Ah.
-...I strongly advise

51
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:52,440
the issuing of scissor grenades,

52
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:56,440
limbo vapour
and triple blast brain-spitters.

53
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:58,120
What for?

54
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,520
Just generally.

55
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:04,640
Remember, we are going to the North.

56
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,480
MRS GILLYFLOWER: Bradford,

57
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:15,360
that Babylon of the moderns,
with its crystal light and its glitter.

58
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:19,680
All a-swarm with
the wretched ruins of humanity.

59
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:22,360
-(CONGREGATION MURMURING)
-Men and women

60
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:25,360
crushed by the Devil's juggernaut.

61
00:04:25,520 --> 00:04:27,480
Moral turpitude

62
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:32,520
can destroy the most delicate of lives.
Believe me, I know.

63
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:34,440
I know.

64
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,680
(CONGREGATION GASPING)

65
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:38,320
My own daughter,

66
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:42,760
blinded in a drunken rage
by my late husband.

67
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,000
-MAN: Disgraceful!
-(ALL GASPING)

68
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:47,520
Her once-beautiful eyes

69
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:51,920
pale and white as mistletoe berries.

70
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,920
And what, my friends, is your story?

71
00:04:56,320 --> 00:05:00,320
Will you be found wanting
when the End of Days is come?

72
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:03,960
When judgement rains down upon us all?

73
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:06,160
Or will you be preserved

74
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:09,520
-against the coming apocalypse?
-(CONGREGATION MURMURS)

75
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:11,400
Do not despair.

76
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:14,280
I offer a way out.

77
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:17,440
There is a different path.

78
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:18,960
Sweetville.

79
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:20,880
(CONGREGATION GASPING)

80
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:25,520
-Wow.
-(CONGREGATION CHATTERING)

81
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:31,880
Join us! Join us
in this shining city on the hill.

82
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:36,720
ALL: # Bring me my bow

83
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:40,200
# Of burning gold

84
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:45,600
# Bring me my arrows of desire #

85
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,280
You wish to join us, my dear?

86
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:52,120
If it's all the same with you, ma'am.

87
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:54,840
Oh, yes, dear, you'll do very nicely.

88
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,960
If our stratagem succeeds,

89
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:04,800
Jenny will infiltrate deep into
the black heart of this curious place.

90
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:06,600
And how will she locate the Doctor?

91
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:10,360
To find him, she needs only
ignore all "keep out"” signs,

92
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:12,200
go through every locked door

93
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:16,040
and run towards any form of danger
that presents itself.

94
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:19,480
-Business as usual, then?
-Business as usual.

95
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:36,280
(CHAINS CLINKING)

96
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:56,880
Did you think I'd forgotten you,
dear monster?

97
00:06:56,960 --> 00:06:58,120
-Hmm?
-(BANGS)

98
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,280
(GASPS)

99
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:21,680
I have travelled from London
expressly to see Madame Vastra.

100
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:24,200
Will you be so kind as to
announce me, my good man?

101
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:26,320
STRAX: Who shall I say is calling?

102
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:31,760
(THUDDING)

103
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:38,320
It asked permission to enter,
and then it fell over.

104
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:40,520
What are we to make of it?

105
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:44,560
I imagine Mr Thursday wants to know
what progress we are making.

106
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:47,080
The question is

107
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:50,680
how did the Doctor's image come to
be preserved in a dead man's eye?

108
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:52,480
It's a scientific impossibility.

109
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:54,880
I wonder how Jenny is getting on?

110
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:57,720
If she hasn't made contact by nightfall,
I suggest

111
00:07:57,800 --> 00:08:00,200
a massive frontal assault
on the factory, Madame.

112
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:04,160
Casualties could be kept to
perhaps as little as 80%.

113
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:08,680
I think there may be subtler ways
of proceeding, Strax.

114
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:10,840
Suit yourself.

115
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,160
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

116
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,960
I'm dead nervous, aren't you?

117
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,200
They have to be sure, you see.

118
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,720
Only the best for Sweetville.

119
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:34,840
I hope me teeth don't let me down.
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

120
00:08:36,160 --> 00:08:37,640
I'm Abigail.

121
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:40,000
-Pleased to meet you.
-You're not local, are you?

122
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:41,680
No. Up from London.

123
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:43,680
-Different here, I bet.
-Oh, yeah.

124
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:46,400
-A bleeding horse market.
-(CHUCKLES)

125
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,280
Do you know anyone
who's come to live here?

126
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:52,560
-In Sweetville, I mean?
-(STAMMERS)

127
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:55,000
I had a pal who come here
three month back.

128
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:57,840
She wrote to tell me
how perfect it all were.

129
00:08:57,920 --> 00:09:01,240
Funny, though. I've not heard a peep
from her since.

130
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,760
MAN: Next, please.

131
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:04,640
ABIGAIL: Hang on, we're moving.

132
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,720
What are you doing?

133
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:15,880
Do me a favour, cause a distraction.

134
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,680
-What?
-Swoon.

135
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:19,120
Have a funny turn.

136
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:21,320
-Fit of the vapours.
-Are you crackers?

137
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:22,680
Go on.

138
00:09:22,760 --> 00:09:24,360
There's a guinea in it for you.

139
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:26,120
Done.

140
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,600
(GASPING DRAMATICALLY)

141
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:32,280
(CROWD MURMURING)

142
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:43,200
(LOUD RHYTHMIC CLANGING)

143
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:04,560
(CLANGING CONTINUES)

144
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:24,880
Them new manufacturers can
do horrible things to a person.

145
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:26,320
Horrible!

146
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:28,720
I've pickled things in here

147
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:33,920
that'll fair turn your hair snowy
as top of Buckden Pike.

148
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:38,080
-You know what I'm looking for?
-Oh, aye.

149
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:40,480
All them bits found in t'canal.

150
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:42,680
The Crimson Horror.

151
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:54,560
(EXHALES)

152
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:57,800
It hardly seems possible.

153
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:00,400
-Eh?
-I think...

154
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:05,040
I think I have seen
these symptoms before.

155
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:06,280
Oh, aye?

156
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:09,160
-A long time ago.
-Oh, aye, how long?

157
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:12,880
About 65 million years.

158
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:15,440
(SLURPING)

159
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:20,080
I trust you had a pleasant day, Mama?

160
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,640
Tolerable.

161
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:27,360
Will Mr Sweet ever join us
for dinner, Mama?

162
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:31,560
Mr Sweet is rather tired tonight,
I fear.

163
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:38,240
Oh, dear me. (CHUCKLING)

164
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:40,680
How clumsy I'm getting.

165
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:43,080
To keep the devil at bay.

166
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:14,760
(LIQUIDS BUBBLING INSIDE)

167
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,760
(METALLIC CLANG)

168
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:27,000
(CLANGING CONTINUES)

169
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:44,240
(CLANGING CONTINUES)

170
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,480
(DOORKNOB RATTLES)

171
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:02,200
(SHRIEKS)

172
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:12,640
All right, mate.

173
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:14,720
You just stay calm, now.

174
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:15,880
(BANGS)

175
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:23,520
I could open this door.
Would you like that?

176
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:25,920
(BANGS)

177
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:27,720
I thought you might.

178
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:32,520
But you and me has got
to come to an arrangement,

179
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:35,640
-savvy?
-(BANGS)

180
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:40,000
Now, you stand well back,
do you hear me?

181
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:44,280
I don't mean no harm to you,
but you try anything funny

182
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:46,360
and I'll leave you here to rot.

183
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:49,400
-Is that understood?
-(BANGS TWICE)

184
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:51,680
Right.

185
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,200
(GASPS) Doctor!

186
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:06,280
(GROANING)

187
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:09,040
What happened to you?

188
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:13,120
Ah, ah, ah... (GROANS)

189
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:19,120
-Can't you speak?
-(GROANING)

190
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:22,800
-(MAKES A HOLLOW SOUND)
-(GASPS)

191
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:27,480
Right. Well, we're getting out of here.

192
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:28,880
(DOCTOR GROANING)

193
00:14:30,760 --> 00:14:32,200
(DOCTOR GRUNTING)

194
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:40,920
-Come on.
-(GROANS)

195
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:44,800
Come on.

196
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:47,280
(DOCTOR GRUNTING)

197
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:03,600
(BUBBLING)

198
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:24,880
Oh, my God!

199
00:15:31,160 --> 00:15:32,280
(GRUNTING)

200
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:42,720
You are all I have, monster.

201
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:47,080
But all will be well.
Imperfect as we are,

202
00:15:47,160 --> 00:15:49,800
there will be room for us
in the new Jerusalem.

203
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:50,960
(DOOR CREAKS)

204
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:03,440
No. No!

205
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:06,960
Where are you, monster? Where are you?

206
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:08,640
(DOCTOR GRUNTING)

207
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:17,040
-You want to go in there?
-(GRUNTS LOUDLY)

208
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:23,360
(GRUNTING)

209
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:50,400
-Ha! Miss me?
-Doctor!

210
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:53,240
Jenny! Jenny, Jenny, Jenny, Jenny.

211
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:57,160
Just when you think your favourite
lock-picking Victorian chambermaid

212
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:59,120
will never turn up,

213
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,400
-Jenny!
-(GASPS)

214
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:03,840
(GROANS)

215
00:17:04,520 --> 00:17:06,880
You have no idea
how good that feels. Ooh!

216
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:09,760
Right! Mrs Gillyflower,
we've got to stop her.

217
00:17:09,840 --> 00:17:11,680
And then there's Clara. Poor Clara.
Where's Clara?

218
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:12,960
Clara?

219
00:17:13,040 --> 00:17:15,040
-Doctor, wait!
-Can't, Clara, got to find.

220
00:17:15,120 --> 00:17:17,840
What happened to you?
How long have you been like that?

221
00:17:17,920 --> 00:17:20,400
Days, weeks? Don't know. Long story.

222
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:22,240
I'll keep it short.

223
00:17:22,320 --> 00:17:24,160
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

224
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:27,400
Okay, so...

225
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:31,240
Not London, 1893.

226
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:33,760
Yorkshire, 1893. Near enough.

227
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:36,560
You're making a habit of this,
getting us lost.

228
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:39,320
Sorry. It's much better
than it used to be.

229
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:42,440
Ooh, I once spent a hell of a long time
trying to get a gobby Australian

230
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:43,960
to Heathrow Airport.

231
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,920
-What for?
-Search me. Anyway...

232
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,400
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

233
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:51,000
Brave heart, Clara.

234
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:54,240
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

235
00:17:56,040 --> 00:17:57,400
EDMUND: It's another one. Don't you see?

236
00:17:57,480 --> 00:18:00,240
Another victim!
Why won't any one of you listen?

237
00:18:00,560 --> 00:18:01,800
We'll listen.

238
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:03,000
(CAMERA CLICKING)

239
00:18:03,080 --> 00:18:05,720
EDMUND: Mrs Winifred Gillyflower,
an astonishing woman.

240
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:08,560
Prize-winning chemist
and mechanical engineer, so why?

241
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:12,080
Why has she decided to open up
a match factory in her old hometown?

242
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:15,920
And no one who ever goes to live there
ever seems to come out.

243
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:22,240
Same as the rest.

244
00:18:22,520 --> 00:18:24,520
All dead from causes unknown
and their flesh...

245
00:18:25,280 --> 00:18:28,520
Glowing. Like something manky
in a coal cellar.

246
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:30,600
They keep turning up in t'canal.

247
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:32,240
The Crimson Horror.

248
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:34,480
Ooh, good name!

249
00:18:34,840 --> 00:18:37,720
Hey, that's good, isn't it?
The Crimson Horror.

250
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:40,520
(CHUCKLES) I wonder what it is?

251
00:18:42,560 --> 00:18:46,000
Do you know
the old Romany superstition, Clara,

252
00:18:46,120 --> 00:18:49,880
that the eye of a dead person retains
an image of the last thing it sees?

253
00:18:49,960 --> 00:18:51,400
Nonsense, of course.

254
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:53,840
Unless the chemical composition
of the body

255
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:55,680
has been massively corrupted.

256
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:05,760
Wow, this is nasty. An organic poison,

257
00:19:05,840 --> 00:19:09,400
a sort of venom. And you think
it's connected to Sweetville?

258
00:19:09,480 --> 00:19:11,640
-I do.
-Well, then,

259
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:12,880
we need a plan.

260
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:18,400
Doctor and Mrs Smith.
(CHUCKLES) Oh, yes!

261
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:19,840
You'll do very nicely.

262
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:22,560
Oh, grand! Smashing!

263
00:19:22,640 --> 00:19:25,080
Hey, the missus and I couldn't be
more chuffed. Could we, love?

264
00:19:25,520 --> 00:19:26,800
-Huh?
-(GIGGLES)

265
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:32,720
Sweetville will provide you
with everything you need.

266
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:35,320
You won't have to worry about a thing
ever again.

267
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:37,840
-The name, Sweetville...
-Yes.

268
00:19:37,920 --> 00:19:40,320
Why not name it after yourself?
After all, it's your creation.

269
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:41,960
Gillyflower Town, eh?

270
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:44,680
Gillyflower Land,
you could have rollercoasters.

271
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:47,400
It is named in tribute to my partner.

272
00:19:47,480 --> 00:19:49,720
-Your late partner?
-No. My...

273
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:51,720
silent partner.

274
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:54,000
Mr Sweet likes to
keep himself to himself.

275
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:55,440
Shall we move on?

276
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:59,240
-Who lives here?
-(CHUCKLES) Oh, names don't matter here.

277
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:03,160
All you need to know is we only
recruit the brightest and the best.

278
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:22,800
(GASPING)

279
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:26,920
Like pretty maids all in a row.

280
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:29,760
The process improves with every attempt.

281
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:32,800
Mr Sweet is such a clever old thing.

282
00:20:33,280 --> 00:20:34,440
Oh!

283
00:20:34,520 --> 00:20:37,600
Into the canal with the rejects, Ada.

284
00:20:37,680 --> 00:20:38,760
Yes.

285
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:42,840
(MAN GROANING)

286
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:49,000
(ADA GASPS)

287
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:57,600
Sometimes the preservation process
goes wrong.

288
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:00,480
Only Mr Sweet knows why.

289
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:03,000
And only Mama is allowed
to talk to Mr Sweet.

290
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:07,320
But if you're very good,
you can stay here.

291
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:11,080
(WHISPERS) You'll be my secret.

292
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:12,800
My special monster.

293
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:16,320
Shh. (GIGGLES)

294
00:21:20,840 --> 00:21:23,080
(DOCTOR GRUNTING)

295
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:29,760
(SCREAMS)

296
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:32,480
(DOOR OPENS)

297
00:21:32,560 --> 00:21:34,960
(SCREAMING)

298
00:21:39,720 --> 00:21:40,760
(THUDDING)

299
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:42,360
(GRUNTING)

300
00:21:45,520 --> 00:21:47,480
Poor Edmund
must have come looking for us

301
00:21:47,560 --> 00:21:50,680
and then fallen into a vat
of the pure venom.

302
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:54,480
Or was pushed.
He didn't stand a chance.

303
00:21:54,560 --> 00:21:56,000
What is that stuff, though?

304
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:57,840
Deadly poison.

305
00:21:57,920 --> 00:22:00,680
And Mrs Gillyflower has been dipping
her pilgrims in a dilute form

306
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:02,440
to protect and preserve them.

307
00:22:02,520 --> 00:22:05,080
Process didn't work on me,
maybe because I am not human.

308
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:07,080
I ended up on the reject pile.

309
00:22:08,120 --> 00:22:09,360
Preserve them against what?

310
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:12,360
Well, according to her,
the coming apocalypse.

311
00:22:12,440 --> 00:22:13,560
(WHISTLING)

312
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:18,640
"When the End of Days has come
and judgement rains down upon us all..."

313
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:20,520
What?

314
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:21,880
-Nothing.
-No, no, no. What?

315
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:25,160
Something Mrs Gillyflower said
in one of her sermons.

316
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:28,200
Madame will come looking for me.
We best get on.

317
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:30,040
Yes, Clara, got to find Clara.

318
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:32,040
But Doctor...

319
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:34,440
Clara's dead.

320
00:22:34,600 --> 00:22:35,760
Isn't she?

321
00:22:38,120 --> 00:22:39,960
It's complicated.

322
00:22:45,880 --> 00:22:49,080
Horse, you have failed in your mission.

323
00:22:49,360 --> 00:22:51,920
We're lost, with no sign of Sweetville.

324
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:55,360
Do you have any final words
before your summary execution?

325
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:56,920
(SNUFFLES)

326
00:22:58,440 --> 00:23:00,120
The usual story.

327
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:04,160
Fourth one this week,
and I'm not even hungry.

328
00:23:04,320 --> 00:23:05,560
BOY: Sweetville, sir?

329
00:23:07,280 --> 00:23:09,440
-Do you know it?
-Turn around when possible,

330
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:12,040
then, at the end of the road,
turn right.

331
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:14,160
-What?
-Bear left for a quarter of a mile,

332
00:23:14,240 --> 00:23:16,400
you will have reached your destination.

333
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:26,600
Thank you. What is your name?

334
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:29,040
Thomas, sir. Thomas Thomas.

335
00:23:29,120 --> 00:23:31,640
I think you will do well, Thomas Thomas.

336
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:38,640
Are we talking about the same person,
about that Clara?

337
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:40,920
Doctor!

338
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:44,200
-What...
-(DOOR CLOSES)

339
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:46,880
I couldn't see much from where I was
but I think

340
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:49,320
she survived the process.
She must be here somewhere.

341
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:50,920
But Clara died!

342
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,440
-The ice lady...
-(DOOR CLOSES)

343
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:54,600
Doctor!

344
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:56,720
(STAMMERING) Uh...

345
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:58,280
(WHISPERS) It's complicated.

346
00:24:09,520 --> 00:24:10,640
(YELLS)

347
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:15,320
(SOBBING)

348
00:24:17,880 --> 00:24:20,920
What is the meaning of this?

349
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:23,080
(SOBBING) Oh, Mama!

350
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:25,800
I have been foolish.

351
00:24:26,040 --> 00:24:29,320
(SNIFFLES) I have formed a...

352
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:32,440
sentimental attachment.

353
00:24:32,520 --> 00:24:35,280
An attachment? To whom?

354
00:24:35,360 --> 00:24:36,840
A young man.

355
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:39,840
Unlike the others,
he survived rejection.

356
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:42,480
He must be strong, worthy of salvation.

357
00:24:42,560 --> 00:24:44,520
Wrecker. Berserker!

358
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:47,760
You have loosed a reject
onto the outside world.

359
00:24:47,840 --> 00:24:50,880
-I have disappointed you.
-My plans must be accelerated.

360
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:53,800
Nothing must interfere
with the great work.

361
00:24:53,880 --> 00:24:57,120
But please say there is still room
for me in your new Eden, Mama,

362
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:59,520
-promise me that.
-I'll set my pilgrims onto him.

363
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:00,960
No!

364
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:05,960
Kindly do not claw and slobber
at my crinoline.

365
00:25:06,080 --> 00:25:08,840
You know I cannot bear
to look at sick people.

366
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:10,960
Promise me you will not
abandon me, Mama.

367
00:25:11,040 --> 00:25:14,120
-Promise me that.
-Do you not yet understand?

368
00:25:14,840 --> 00:25:17,720
There can be no place
for people such as you.

369
00:25:18,040 --> 00:25:22,200
And only perfection is good enough
for myself and Mr Sweet.

370
00:25:22,280 --> 00:25:24,000
(SOBBING)

371
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:26,800
The bright day is done, child,

372
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:29,600
and you are for the dark.

373
00:25:32,040 --> 00:25:33,240
(SOBBING)

374
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:40,080
JENNY: Can she be revived like you were?

375
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:41,920
I hope so.

376
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:48,120
JENNY: Doctor!

377
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:50,880
Oh, great, great!

378
00:25:50,960 --> 00:25:52,560
Attack of the supermodels.

379
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:55,080
Time for a plan.

380
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:57,400
No, Doctor, this one's on me.

381
00:26:06,480 --> 00:26:08,240
(BOTH GRUNTING)

382
00:26:13,280 --> 00:26:14,840
That is a plan.

383
00:26:16,080 --> 00:26:17,840
Okay, time for a new plan.

384
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:18,960
-Run!
-(GASPS)

385
00:26:19,040 --> 00:26:22,320
STRAX: Sontar ha! (CACKLING)

386
00:26:25,720 --> 00:26:27,000
(LAUGHING)

387
00:26:28,360 --> 00:26:30,160
-Let's go!
-No, ma'am, we're not escaping.

388
00:26:30,320 --> 00:26:32,360
We've got to help the Doctor with Clara.

389
00:26:36,320 --> 00:26:37,440
Long story.

390
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:40,760
What now, Madame? We could
lay my magnetic cluster bands!

391
00:26:40,840 --> 00:26:42,320
-Strax...
-Or dig trenches

392
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:45,320
-and fill them with acid.
-Strax! You're overexcited.

393
00:26:45,400 --> 00:26:48,120
Have you been eating
those jelly sherbet fancies again?

394
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:50,720
No.

395
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:52,600
Go outside and wait for me
until I call for you.

396
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:54,160
-But Madame...
-Go!

397
00:26:55,560 --> 00:26:56,720
(GRUNTS)

398
00:26:56,800 --> 00:26:58,960
(MUMBLING) I'm going
to go play with my grenades.

399
00:27:00,280 --> 00:27:02,960
Okay. I think she's about done.

400
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:06,080
(DOCTOR GRUNTS)

401
00:27:07,360 --> 00:27:10,200
I know who you think she is,
but she isn't.

402
00:27:10,880 --> 00:27:12,040
(WHISPERS) She can't be.

403
00:27:12,120 --> 00:27:15,680
I was right, then, you and Clara
have unfinished business.

404
00:27:17,280 --> 00:27:19,080
Hey, hey!

405
00:27:19,600 --> 00:27:21,040
-Hello, stranger.
-(CHUCKLES)

406
00:27:22,280 --> 00:27:23,640
-Doctor.
-Yeah.

407
00:27:23,720 --> 00:27:24,760
-Uh-huh.
-(CHUCKLES)

408
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:26,800
Hi.

409
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:30,680
What's going on?

410
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:35,080
Oh. Haven't you heard, love?
There's trouble at mill.

411
00:27:36,960 --> 00:27:38,200
She's a lizard.

412
00:27:40,320 --> 00:27:43,280
My people once ruled this world,
as well you know,

413
00:27:43,360 --> 00:27:44,720
but we did not rule it alone.

414
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:48,800
Just as humanity fights a daily battle
against nature, so did we.

415
00:27:48,880 --> 00:27:51,840
And our greatest plague,
the most virulent enemy,

416
00:27:52,320 --> 00:27:53,920
was a repulsive red leech.

417
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:56,720
Ooh, the repulsive red leech.

418
00:27:57,240 --> 00:27:59,040
Now, on balance,
I think I prefer the Crimson Horror.

419
00:27:59,120 --> 00:28:00,200
What was it, exactly?

420
00:28:00,280 --> 00:28:02,840
A tiny parasite.
It infected our drinking water.

421
00:28:02,920 --> 00:28:05,760
Once in our systems,
it secreted a fatal poison.

422
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:07,760
It's been hanging around,

423
00:28:07,840 --> 00:28:11,440
lurking in the shadows.
Maybe it's evolved.

424
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:13,960
Maybe it's had help.

425
00:28:14,240 --> 00:28:15,840
Doctor, I've been thinking.

426
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:17,040
-The chimney...
-Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah,

427
00:28:17,120 --> 00:28:18,240
way past that now.

428
00:28:18,320 --> 00:28:20,200
Yucky red parasite
from the time of the dinosaurs

429
00:28:20,280 --> 00:28:21,840
pitches up in Victorian Yorkshire.

430
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:23,480
-Didn't see that one coming.
-Yeah, but the chimney...

431
00:28:23,560 --> 00:28:25,200
Yeah, but what's the connection
to Mrs Gillyflower?

432
00:28:25,280 --> 00:28:27,800
"Judgement will rain down on us all.”

433
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:33,800
An empty mill...

434
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:37,840
A chimney that doesn't blow smoke.

435
00:28:41,960 --> 00:28:43,120
Clever-clogs.

436
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:44,680
-Miss me?
-Yeah, lots.

437
00:28:52,360 --> 00:28:54,920
-She's going to poison the air.
-How?

438
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:57,120
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

439
00:29:05,760 --> 00:29:08,040
With that, I should think.

440
00:29:11,160 --> 00:29:12,960
DOCTOR: And there's the poison.

441
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:16,800
All right, gang, I've got a plan.

442
00:29:18,040 --> 00:29:20,200
(METAL CLANGS ON FLOOR)

443
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:25,000
Okay.

444
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:51,760
(ADA SOBBING)

445
00:29:56,640 --> 00:29:57,720
Who is it?

446
00:29:58,160 --> 00:29:59,240
Who is there?

447
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:04,520
Okay.

448
00:30:08,920 --> 00:30:10,000
You...

449
00:30:10,320 --> 00:30:12,640
It's you, my monster.

450
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:14,120
You've come back.

451
00:30:14,200 --> 00:30:16,360
-But you're...
-Warm and alive.

452
00:30:16,760 --> 00:30:18,440
Thanks to you, Ada.

453
00:30:18,520 --> 00:30:21,520
You saved me from
your mother's human rubbish tip.

454
00:30:21,640 --> 00:30:23,880
Now, hey. What's wrong?

455
00:30:24,840 --> 00:30:27,520
She does not want me, monster.

456
00:30:27,880 --> 00:30:29,440
I am not to be chosen.

457
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:32,360
Perhaps it was my own sin.

458
00:30:32,720 --> 00:30:35,320
The blackness in my heart
that my father saw in me.

459
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:36,680
Ada, no!

460
00:30:36,760 --> 00:30:40,080
That's nonsense,
stupid, backwards nonsense,

461
00:30:40,160 --> 00:30:41,320
and you know it.

462
00:30:42,520 --> 00:30:43,800
(SOFTLY) You know it.

463
00:30:48,680 --> 00:30:49,960
-CLARA: What is it?
-Who is that?

464
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:51,520
I'm...

465
00:30:53,840 --> 00:30:56,240
I'm a friend.

466
00:30:56,320 --> 00:30:57,440
A friend of his.

467
00:30:57,520 --> 00:31:00,000
ADA: Then you are fortunate indeed.

468
00:31:00,080 --> 00:31:02,840
It isn't good to be alone. (SIGHS)

469
00:31:03,360 --> 00:31:04,640
DOCTOR: Now, Ada,

470
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:07,320
I need you to tell me something.

471
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:11,680
Who is Mr Sweet?

472
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:13,280
Ada...

473
00:31:13,600 --> 00:31:15,280
Oh, dear monster.

474
00:31:15,360 --> 00:31:16,800
-Please.
-I cannot.

475
00:31:16,880 --> 00:31:20,360
Even now, I cannot.
I cannot betray Mama.

476
00:31:23,040 --> 00:31:24,360
(SOBBING)

477
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:26,840
Well, come with us, then.

478
00:31:28,320 --> 00:31:30,160
There is something you need to know.

479
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:51,000
(CHUCKLING) Oh, you do seem
to keep turning up

480
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:53,320
-like a bad penny, young man.
-Force of habit.

481
00:31:53,720 --> 00:31:55,040
Can I offer you something?

482
00:31:55,120 --> 00:31:57,040
Tea? Seed cake? (GASPS)

483
00:31:57,120 --> 00:31:58,960
A glass of amontillado?

484
00:31:59,040 --> 00:32:01,760
No, thanks, we've had a skinful already,
as you might say.

485
00:32:01,840 --> 00:32:03,040
(CHUCKLES) Very funny.

486
00:32:03,120 --> 00:32:07,040
Hmm, yes. I'm the Doctor,
you're nuts and I'm going to stop you.

487
00:32:07,120 --> 00:32:10,440
I am afraid Mr Sweet and I
cannot allow that.

488
00:32:10,520 --> 00:32:12,240
Ah, yes. Would it be impolite to ask

489
00:32:12,320 --> 00:32:14,680
why you and Mr Sweet are petrifying
your workforce

490
00:32:14,760 --> 00:32:17,280
with diluted prehistoric leech venom?

491
00:32:17,360 --> 00:32:19,040
So, when do we get to meet him,

492
00:32:19,120 --> 00:32:21,680
this silent partner of yours?
Why is he so shy?

493
00:32:21,760 --> 00:32:24,160
Mr Sweet is always with us.

494
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:27,320
You do seem to have a very
close relationship, you and your pal.

495
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:30,160
Oh, yes, Doctor. Exceedingly close.

496
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:34,520
Symbiotic, you might say.

497
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:53,480
Doctor, what is it?

498
00:32:53,560 --> 00:32:54,880
A survivor.

499
00:32:54,960 --> 00:32:59,400
He has grown fat on the filth
humanity has pumped into the rivers.

500
00:32:59,800 --> 00:33:01,120
That's where I found him.

501
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:03,320
-Very enterprising.
-His needs are simple.

502
00:33:03,400 --> 00:33:05,760
And in return he gives me his nectar.

503
00:33:05,840 --> 00:33:07,240
Mrs Gillyflower,

504
00:33:08,600 --> 00:33:10,920
you have no idea
what you are dealing with.

505
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:15,400
In the wrong hands, that venom
could wipe out all life on this planet.

506
00:33:15,840 --> 00:33:17,120
Do you know what these are?

507
00:33:19,400 --> 00:33:22,120
(LAUGHING) The wrong hands.

508
00:33:37,680 --> 00:33:39,720
Planning a little fireworks party,
are we?

509
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:43,480
You have forced me to advance
the great work somewhat, Doctor.

510
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:46,840
But my colossal scheme
remains as it was.

511
00:33:47,080 --> 00:33:50,280
My rocket will explode
high in the atmosphere,

512
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:54,760
raining down Mr Sweet's beneficence
onto all humanity.

513
00:33:54,840 --> 00:33:56,560
And wiping us all out. You can't!

514
00:33:56,640 --> 00:34:00,160
My new Adam and Eves will sleep
but for a few months

515
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:03,680
before stepping out into a golden dawn.

516
00:34:03,760 --> 00:34:05,640
Is it not beautiful, Doctor?

517
00:34:08,720 --> 00:34:12,640
Now, tell us about Ada, Mrs Gillyflower.

518
00:34:12,720 --> 00:34:13,880
-What?
-Your daughter.

519
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:17,520
You do remember your daughter?
Tell us about your daughter.

520
00:34:17,600 --> 00:34:21,320
How can you speak of such trivia
when my hour is at hand?

521
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:23,560
The child is of no consequence.

522
00:34:23,640 --> 00:34:25,360
Is that why you experimented on her?

523
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:27,720
CLARA: Experimented?
DOCTOR: The signs are all there.

524
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:28,840
The pattern of scarring.

525
00:34:28,920 --> 00:34:32,120
You used her as a guinea pig,
didn't you?

526
00:34:32,200 --> 00:34:35,280
-God!
-Sometimes sacrifices must be made.

527
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:40,800
-Sacrifices?
-It was necessary.

528
00:34:40,880 --> 00:34:44,440
I had to find out how much of the venom
would produce an antitoxin

529
00:34:44,520 --> 00:34:46,720
to immunise myself, don't you see?

530
00:34:46,800 --> 00:34:48,360
It was necessary!

531
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:51,160
Mama? Is it...

532
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:53,000
Is it true?

533
00:34:53,080 --> 00:34:55,400
-Ada...
-It is!

534
00:34:56,160 --> 00:34:59,960
-It's true. True!
-Ada, listen to me.

535
00:35:00,040 --> 00:35:01,440
You hag!

536
00:35:02,120 --> 00:35:04,200
You perfidious hag!

537
00:35:04,960 --> 00:35:07,960
You virago! You harpy!

538
00:35:08,040 --> 00:35:09,920
All these years I have helped you,

539
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:13,400
served you, looked after you,
does it count for nothing?

540
00:35:13,800 --> 00:35:15,160
Nothing at all!

541
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:18,200
MRS GILLYFLOWER: Oh, stop!
Stop! Oh!

542
00:35:19,520 --> 00:35:21,600
Hang on, hang on,
I've got a sonic screwdriver.

543
00:35:21,680 --> 00:35:24,160
Yeah? I've got a chair. (GRUNTS)

544
00:35:24,360 --> 00:35:25,400
No!

545
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:30,000
DOCTOR: Yeah.

546
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:32,040
That worked.

547
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:36,640
I'm afraid your rocket
isn't going anywhere, Mrs G.

548
00:35:36,720 --> 00:35:38,520
(MRS GILLYFLOWER SOBBING)

549
00:35:52,120 --> 00:35:55,640
Please, come to me, Ada.

550
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:58,200
(ADA SOBBING)

551
00:35:58,280 --> 00:36:01,480
Oh, my child.

552
00:36:02,240 --> 00:36:06,000
You have always been so very

553
00:36:06,760 --> 00:36:08,200
useful.

554
00:36:08,680 --> 00:36:10,560
No, Mrs Gillyflower.

555
00:36:10,640 --> 00:36:13,240
Please, Mama, no more, no more.

556
00:36:13,320 --> 00:36:17,800
And now, if you will forgive us,
we must be going.

557
00:36:17,880 --> 00:36:21,720
It is long past Ada's bedtime.

558
00:36:22,800 --> 00:36:23,880
No, no, Clara.

559
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:26,280
If we follow straight after her,
she'll shoot Ada on the spot.

560
00:36:26,360 --> 00:36:27,880
-She wouldn't!
-She would.

561
00:36:31,280 --> 00:36:32,840
Chairs are useful.

562
00:36:34,520 --> 00:36:35,760
(GRUNTING)

563
00:36:35,840 --> 00:36:37,080
(GLASS SHATTERING)

564
00:36:37,160 --> 00:36:38,960
Come along, Ada, don't dawdle.

565
00:36:39,040 --> 00:36:40,640
Please, Mama, stop!

566
00:36:41,080 --> 00:36:42,560
Has the venom been loaded?

567
00:36:42,640 --> 00:36:44,920
-Yes, ma'am.
-Then heaven awaits you.

568
00:37:06,040 --> 00:37:07,440
ADA: Stop!

569
00:37:12,720 --> 00:37:14,160
Just let her go.

570
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:16,480
Mrs Gillyflower, let Ada go.

571
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:18,840
Secondary firing mechanism, Doctor.

572
00:37:18,960 --> 00:37:21,680
Mr Sweet and I were too smart
for you after all.

573
00:37:21,760 --> 00:37:24,280
Just let your daughter go,
Mrs Gillyflower.

574
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:26,240
-(SOBBING) Monster!
-Ada!

575
00:37:26,360 --> 00:37:27,480
(ADA GROANS)

576
00:37:28,800 --> 00:37:30,600
Shoot if you wish, Mama.

577
00:37:30,680 --> 00:37:34,160
It is of no matter,
for you killed me a long time ago.

578
00:37:39,880 --> 00:37:42,560
# I'll lab our night and day

579
00:37:42,640 --> 00:37:45,480
# To be a pilgrim #

580
00:37:56,760 --> 00:37:58,760
(CACKLING)

581
00:38:03,880 --> 00:38:05,840
Now, Mr Sweet.

582
00:38:06,160 --> 00:38:10,920
Now the whole world will taste
your lethal kiss.

583
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:13,600
I don't think so, Mrs Gillyflower.

584
00:38:13,680 --> 00:38:14,840
(SNAPS FINGERS)

585
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:19,360
MRS GILLYFLOWER: Oh!

586
00:38:20,160 --> 00:38:21,520
Very well, then.

587
00:38:21,600 --> 00:38:23,960
If I can't take the world with me,

588
00:38:24,040 --> 00:38:26,240
you will have to do.

589
00:38:26,320 --> 00:38:29,040
Die, you freaks!

590
00:38:29,120 --> 00:38:30,200
Die!

591
00:38:30,480 --> 00:38:33,520
-Die!
-STRAX: Put down your weapon,

592
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:35,440
human female.

593
00:38:35,520 --> 00:38:36,880
(GASPS)

594
00:38:41,200 --> 00:38:42,320
-Oh.
-(YELLS)

595
00:38:44,080 --> 00:38:45,880
(MRS GILLYFLOWER THUDDING)

596
00:38:46,640 --> 00:38:47,680
Ouch!

597
00:38:59,160 --> 00:39:00,240
No!

598
00:39:00,560 --> 00:39:01,760
No!

599
00:39:02,240 --> 00:39:06,240
Mr Sweet. Where are you going?

600
00:39:07,240 --> 00:39:09,280
You can't leave me now.

601
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:11,400
-Mr Sweet.
-CLARA: Ugh!

602
00:39:11,480 --> 00:39:13,240
-What's it doing?
-It knows she's dying.

603
00:39:13,600 --> 00:39:15,080
She's no longer of any use to it.

604
00:39:15,160 --> 00:39:17,040
MRS GILLYFLOWER: Mr Sweet!

605
00:39:18,040 --> 00:39:20,080
(MRS GILLYFLOWER GROANING)

606
00:39:20,440 --> 00:39:21,480
Ada...

607
00:39:22,640 --> 00:39:23,720
Ada.

608
00:39:24,440 --> 00:39:25,880
(MRS GILLYFLOWER GROANING)

609
00:39:27,560 --> 00:39:29,200
Are you there?

610
00:39:30,680 --> 00:39:31,800
I'm here, Mama.

611
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:36,000
MRS GILLYFLOWER: Forgive me, my child.

612
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:38,040
Forgive me.

613
00:39:41,600 --> 00:39:43,160
Never!

614
00:39:43,400 --> 00:39:46,600
That's my girl.

615
00:39:51,600 --> 00:39:52,680
(ALL GASP)

616
00:39:57,760 --> 00:39:58,840
(WHISTLES)

617
00:40:00,160 --> 00:40:02,240
JENNY: What will you do with that thing?

618
00:40:02,320 --> 00:40:04,960
DOCTOR: Take it back
to the Jurassic era, maybe.

619
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:07,000
Out of harm's way.

620
00:40:10,160 --> 00:40:12,240
(GRUNTING)

621
00:40:15,960 --> 00:40:17,160
(PANTING)

622
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:21,520
On the other hand... Ooh.

623
00:40:22,600 --> 00:40:25,840
Right, right, London.
We were heading for London, weren't we?

624
00:40:25,920 --> 00:40:27,520
Was there any particular reason?

625
00:40:27,600 --> 00:40:29,840
No, no, just thought you might

626
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:32,000
like it.

627
00:40:32,080 --> 00:40:33,160
Yeah.

628
00:40:33,240 --> 00:40:35,080
Maybe had enough
of Victorian values for a bit.

629
00:40:35,160 --> 00:40:37,840
-You're the boss.
-Am I?

630
00:40:38,240 --> 00:40:40,280
No. No! Get in.

631
00:40:44,080 --> 00:40:45,720
(STRAX CHATTING, INDISTINCT)

632
00:40:46,040 --> 00:40:49,000
Now, Ada, I'd love to stay
and help clear up the mess but...

633
00:40:49,080 --> 00:40:51,440
I know, dear monster,
you have things to do.

634
00:40:51,520 --> 00:40:52,640
And what about you?

635
00:40:52,720 --> 00:40:56,600
Oh, there are many things a bright
young lady can do to occupy her time.

636
00:40:57,760 --> 00:41:00,600
It's time I stepped out of
the darkness and into the light.

637
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:02,560
Good luck, Ada.

638
00:41:03,240 --> 00:41:05,920
You know, I think you will be just...

639
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:11,800
splendid!

640
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:19,920
Well! Thanks a million,
you three, as ever.

641
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:21,760
Have some Pontefract cakes on me.

642
00:41:22,320 --> 00:41:24,920
I love Pontefract cakes.
(IMITATES SWORD) Ha!

643
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:26,520
See you around, eh?

644
00:41:26,720 --> 00:41:27,880
I shouldn't wonder.

645
00:41:28,920 --> 00:41:31,960
But Doctor, that girl, Clara...

646
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:34,560
You haven't explained.

647
00:41:43,520 --> 00:41:46,800
(STAMMERS) No, I haven't.

648
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:52,480
Ah, look at the muck in here.

649
00:41:52,560 --> 00:41:53,640
Right.

650
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:57,000
Another one for the vault?

651
00:41:58,920 --> 00:42:00,400
Ah, there you are.

652
00:42:00,800 --> 00:42:02,840
I called to see
if there had been any progress.

653
00:42:02,920 --> 00:42:04,200
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

654
00:42:16,760 --> 00:42:17,840
The boss.

655
00:42:18,480 --> 00:42:19,880
Yep, that's me.

656
00:42:27,720 --> 00:42:29,400
"I am the boss."

657
00:42:43,160 --> 00:42:44,680
It's you, isn't it?

658
00:42:45,320 --> 00:42:48,000
It's from the '70s,
but it's definitely you.

659
00:42:48,080 --> 00:42:49,480
Of course it's not.

660
00:42:50,160 --> 00:42:55,520
And that's you, too.
From 1983, I found it at school.

661
00:42:56,280 --> 00:42:58,920
No, that's just someone
who looks like me.

662
00:42:59,240 --> 00:43:01,600
And that's someone
who looks like your boyfriend.

663
00:43:02,160 --> 00:43:03,400
Is he an alien?

664
00:43:04,080 --> 00:43:06,360
-ANGIE: Why would he be an alien?
-Uh, the chin.

665
00:43:07,120 --> 00:43:08,440
And the time travel?

666
00:43:12,480 --> 00:43:14,800
-That's not right.
-You were in Victorian London?

667
00:43:14,880 --> 00:43:17,720
No, I was in Victorian Yorkshire.

668
00:43:19,280 --> 00:43:21,920
-How come you didn't tell us?
-Time travel, that's so cool!

669
00:43:22,920 --> 00:43:24,240
-Can we have a go?
-Can you have a what?

670
00:43:24,320 --> 00:43:27,400
-We want a shot at the time machine.
-No, no, no, no, no. Listen!

671
00:43:27,480 --> 00:43:30,560
Okay. Or...

672
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:33,560
Wwe'll have to tell Dad
that our nanny's a time traveller.

673
00:43:41,600 --> 00:43:44,160
DOCTOR: Hedgewick's World,
the biggest and best

674
00:43:44,240 --> 00:43:45,920
amusement park there will ever be.

675
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:49,520
It closed down.
Reports of people just vanishing.

676
00:43:50,280 --> 00:43:51,560
No need to panic my young friends.

677
00:43:51,640 --> 00:43:53,760
We all know there are
no more living Cybermen.

678
00:43:53,840 --> 00:43:55,760
Attack formation! Quickly!

679
00:43:55,840 --> 00:43:56,960
Don't wander off.

680
00:43:59,320 --> 00:44:00,440
(SCREAMING)

681
00:44:01,160 --> 00:44:02,720
Take defensive positions.

682
00:44:03,440 --> 00:44:06,480
They're here!

683
00:44:07,120 --> 00:44:10,360
Hail to you, the Doctor,
saviour of the Cybermen!

